 DURBAN - Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa will join thousands of congregants of the Nazareth Baptist Church to celebrate the life and times of its founder leader Prophet Isaiah Shembe at eGibisile Home in Empangeni, KwaZulu-Natal.Ramaphosa s spokesman Ronnie Mamoepa said the deputy president was visiting the church at the invitation of Prophet Unyazilwezulu Shembe.READ: Shembe church politics comes out in courtOn Monday Workers Day Ramaphosa, who is also the deputy president of the African National Congress, enjoyed a hero s welcome in Mpumalanga as he arrived to deliver a speech.African News Agency